✅ Static blocks = run once per class load.
✅ Main class static blocks = always before main().
✅ Other class static blocks = first reference triggers them.
✅ Must be inside class, cannot use instance members.
✅ Multiple static blocks = top-to-bottom execution.
✅ Execution order = class load -> static init -> main() -> instance creation.


  BEST EXAMPLE FOR THIS
  class MainClass {
    static { System.out.println("MainClass static"); }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Inside main");
        Helper.sayHello();
    }
}

class Helper {
    static { System.out.println("Helper static"); }
    static void sayHello() { System.out.println("Hello from Helper"); }
}

output 
MainClass static   // main class static block
Inside main        // main() runs
Helper static      // helper class initialized now
Hello from Helper  // method executes
